3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with multiple agents (UVMSs) working together to achieve a common goal, which falls under the domain of multiagent systems. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a control scheme that uses load sharing coefficients and feedback from local measurements, which can be considered as AI techniques. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computer vision, it is possible that UVMSs may use vision-based sensors for object detection and tracking, which falls under the domain of computer vision.
